      "description": "Presenting a pristine 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a masterclass in lightweight engineering and 50/50 weight distribution. This specimen features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering a seamless power band and high-revving performance. The chassis is anchored by a factory-spec four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical turn-in precision. Meticulously maintained in its original stock configuration, the vacuum systems and apex seals are in peak operational state, ensuring the complex sequential turbochargers spool with zero hesitation. A true showroom-grade example for the discerning purist.",
